# Altair Curriculum — Environment Variable Reference
# ====================================================
# This file is for documentation purposes only.
# Do NOT copy this to .env for local development.
# Auth features are disabled automatically when these
# values are absent, so local dev works without them.
#
# WHERE THE REAL SECRETS LIVE
# ----------------------------
# GitHub Actions injects SUPABASE_URL and SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
# into the build at deploy time via repository secrets.
#
# To set them up:
#   1. Go to your GitHub repository.
#   2. Settings > Secrets and variables > Actions > New repository secret.
#   3. Add two secrets with exactly these names:
#
#        SUPABASE_URL      — your project URL from Supabase > Settings > API
#        SUPABASE_ANON_KEY — the anon/public key from the same page
#
# The workflow file (.github/workflows/deploy.yml) passes these
# secrets to `npm run build` as environment variables. The
# generator reads them via process.env and bakes them into
# every HTML page as window.__SUPABASE_URL__ and
# window.__SUPABASE_ANON_KEY__.
#
# SECURITY NOTE
# -------------
# The anon key is safe to expose in browser code. Supabase
# Row Level Security (defined in supabase/schema.sql) controls
# what the anon key can actually read or write.
# Never add the service_role key to the workflow or frontend code.
#
# REFERENCE VALUES (do not commit real values here)
# --------------------------------------------------
SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-ref.supabase.co
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-public-key-here

